## 8. Build & Deployment

### Decision: EAS Build + EAS Update

**Required setup:**
- EAS CLI: `npm install -g eas-cli`
- Configuration: `eas.json` (root)

**Rationale:**
- Official Expo build service (replaces classic Expo builds)
- Handles iOS/Android code signing automatically
- Cloud builds ensure consistent environment (no "works on my machine")
- EAS Update enables OTA updates (bug fixes without App Store review)
- Free tier sufficient for early development
- Production-grade CI/CD integration (GitHub Actions)

**Build profiles:**
- `development`: Local dev builds with debugging enabled
- `preview`: Internal testing (TestFlight, Firebase App Distribution)
- `production`: App Store / Google Play releases

**Commands:**
```bash
eas build --profile development
eas build --profile production
eas update --branch production  # OTA update
```

**Forbidden alternatives:**
- ❌ Expo classic builds (deprecated)
- ❌ Manual Xcode/Android Studio builds (unless debugging native modules)

