## 15. Dependency Management

### Rules

**Adding new dependencies:**

1. Check if existing dependency solves the problem
2. Evaluate bundle size impact (use `npx bundlephobia <package>`)
3. Verify React Native compatibility
4. Check maintenance status (last updated, GitHub activity)
5. Prefer TypeScript-first libraries
6. Document the decision in PR description

**Forbidden:**
- Installing "nice to have" dependencies
- Duplicate libraries solving the same problem
- Unmaintained packages (no updates in 1+ year)
- Dependencies without TypeScript support

**When unsure:** Ask before installing

