## 17. Forbidden Libraries & Patterns

The following are **explicitly forbidden** without written approval:

### State Management
- ❌ Redux / Redux Toolkit
- ❌ MobX
- ❌ Zustand
- ❌ Recoil
- ❌ Jotai

**Why:** Project uses local state + URQL cache (see [02_development_governance.mdc](./02_development_governance.mdc))

### GraphQL Clients
- ❌ Apollo Client
- ❌ Relay

**Why:** URQL selected (lightweight, sufficient)

### UI Component Libraries
- ❌ React Native Paper
- ❌ React Native Elements
- ❌ NativeBase

**Why:** Build custom components with NativeWind (avoid heavy abstraction)

### Navigation
- ❌ React Navigation standalone (without Expo Router)

**Why:** Expo Router provides cross-platform routing

---

## 18. When to Ask Before Adding a Dependency

Ask the user/team before adding:

1. Any state management library
2. Alternative GraphQL client
3. UI component library
4. Alternative navigation system
5. Build tool changes (Metro, Webpack)
6. Testing framework changes
7. Any package > 100KB
8. Any package solving a problem already solved

